"""
WIPE_AND_RESEED.py - Reset local DB with real customer + product lists.
=======================================================================

What it does (in order):

1. BACKUPS the live SQLite to:
     ~/Documents/NEW_INDIAN_STEEL/backups/billing.db.backup-pre-reseed-<ts>
2. WIPES local tables: invoice_items, invoices, payments, pending_syncs,
   background_tasks, customers, products.
3. RESEEDS:
     - 79 real customers (with opening_balance = current Khatabook due)
     - 1 of those (Jj Traders) has a Cr balance; we insert a "carry-over"
       payment row so get_computed_due returns the correct negative due
       (i.e. WE owe them).
     - 197 real products (id+name+price exactly as listed).
4. PRINTS a summary so you can sanity-check before launching the app.

This script does NOT touch Supabase. Cloud cleanup runs separately
through the MCP, and the next app start will auto-sync the fresh data.

Usage on your laptop / shop PC:

    python WIPE_AND_RESEED.py

You will be asked to type RESEED before anything is wiped. The backup
created in step 1 lets you restore if anything looks wrong:

    Copy backups\billing.db.backup-pre-reseed-<ts>  ->  billing.db
"""
